#: ../../Y/YHBT.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet: very common] Abbreviation: You Have Been Trolled (see "
":ref:`troll`\\, sense 1). Especially used in \"YHBT. YHL. HAND. \", which is"
" widely understood to expand to \"You Have Been Trolled. You Have Lost. Have"
" A Nice Day\". You are quite likely to see this if you respond incautiously "
"to a flame-provoking post that was obviously floated as sucker bait."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet: 非常に一般的] 略語: You Have Been Trolled(おまえは釣られた。\\ :ref:`troll`\\ "
"の語義1を参照)。とくに\"YHBT. YHL. HAND.\"という形で使われ、これは\"You Have Been Trolled. You "
"Have Lost. Have A Nice "
"Day\"(おまえは釣られた。おまえの負けだ。よい一日を)に展開されると広く理解されている。明らかに釣り餌として投下された炎上を誘う投稿に不用意に反応すると、これを目にする可能性がかなり高い。"
